Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: selector
Version: 0.10.1
Summary: WSGI request delegation. (AKA routing.)
Home-page: http://github.com/lukearno/selector/
Author: Luke Arno
Author-email: luke.arno@gmail.com
License: MIT
Description: This distribution provides WSGI middleware for "RESTful" mapping of URL paths to WSGI applications. Selector now also comes with components for environ based dispatch and on-the-fly middleware composition. There is a very simple optional mini-language for path expressions. Alternately we can easily use regular expressions directly or even create our own mini-language. There is a simple "mapping file" format that can be used. There are no architecture specific features (to MVC or whatever). Neither are there any framework specific features.
Keywords: wsgi delegation routing web http rest webapps
Platform: UNKNOWN
